column4: <content>Ad [Addendum] ""BRUEGEL"" Three Soldiers, Frick Collection, cf. Barthel Beham, B. 50 & Sebald Beham, after Barthel Beham, B. 198, reproduced in H.W. Singer, Die Kleinmeister, Künstler Monographien, XLII, Bielefeld & Leipzig, [Velhagen & Klasing],1908, Abb. 7, Abb. 37. The painting, probably by Jan Brueghel, is a free composition developed from the Behams. The slashed sleeves, the feather hat, the drum, the sword of the drummer comparable; cf. also Singer, Abb. 38: Sebald Beham Der Trommler und der Fähnrich.</content>
